    /**
     * Submits a process for execution and returns a Progress representing the pending results of
     * the task.
     *
     * <p>If you would like to immediately block waiting for a task, you can use constructions of
     * the form <tt>result = exec.submit(aProcess).get();</tt>
     *
     * <p>Note: The {@link Processors} class includes a set of methods that can convert some other
     * common closure-like objects, for example, {@link Callable} to {@link Process} form so they
     * can be submitted.
     *
     * @param task the task to submit
     * @return a Progress representing pending completion of the task
     * @throws RejectedExecutionException if task cannot be scheduled for execution
     * @throws NullPointerException if task null
     */
    public Progress submit(Process task, Map<String, Object> input);

